Title: The Prince of Egypt/Joseph: King of Dreams

reviewText: ...and so sometimes folks indicate my reviews were unhelpful. still I won't go into details. I will say these are pretty well done, and King of Dreams is actually pretty close to the Bible. Most of the music is pretty catchy and I actually enjoy watching with my granddaughter. However, they are not for younger children. The Exodus story has some intense history and much of it is here. make sure your child is age appropriate for some slightly intense images of the infamous dreams of the Baker and of Pharoah.

Title: The Prince of Egypt/Joseph: King of Dreams

reviewText: The movies and music are good quality, even though they are not true to Biblical meaning and accuracy (as they claim.)  Prince of Egypt has the best music.  Don't think you understand the true accounts just by watching these, however.  Take them for what they are—hollywood stories—and enjoy.
Title: The Prince of Egypt/Joseph: King of Dreams
